#month-banner("Two", "One", "The Universal Seed in Water", "Catching starlight and rotting morning dew — The preparation of the undetermined")

#v(0.8em)

#hm-note[
  Month 1 of Year Two is arguably the most critical operative month of the entire
  curriculum. The student moves from the "determined" kingdom of plants to the
  "undetermined" kingdom of water. The preparation of the Archaeus of Water is
  long, slow, and demands absolute precision in both timing and sensory
  observation. The formation of the Gur is the threshold: if the Gur does not
  form, the mineral work of Year Three will have no foundation. Monitor students
  closely for the quality of their dew collection and their patience during the
  long putrefaction.
]

